rComments: Reading the textbook is a must to do well in this class. It is hard to understand course material strictly from lecture. Apart from 1-2 difficult questions, tests are 100% fair and come straight from homework problems. Assignments are free marks. He is a good choice for a prof, and is a must if you are interested in logic.

Had him 3 times. He's very passionate about logic. Clear and fair course structure. I think everybody appreciated not having a final exam. As a math student I found the content quite easy but some students with humanities background found it challenging. He was very helpful at office hours and nice to all students even if you never come to class.
Consistently emphasized the big picture. Was very knowledgeable and enthusiastic, and was always up for discussing deeper parts of the material that we didn't necessary have the time to cover.
